# Formally verify persisted inbound queue replay invariants and reset semantics

## Requirements

- Formally or spec-orientedly verify the highest-value persisted inbound queue safety properties after the runtime implementation lands.
- Focus on the behaviors that are easiest to regress silently: ordering, reset semantics, history insertion semantics, and startup ordering.
- Cross-check the proof/spec claims against the documented at-least-once runtime contract.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Verification work covers per-session FIFO replay, no history insertion before processing, reset clears pending rows, and startup replay ordering relative to pending agent resume.
- Any proof assumptions or unverified gaps are documented explicitly rather than implied away.
- Runtime docs remain aligned with the verified/spec-checked behavior, especially the at-least-once semantics.
